qas.question: What are the General Categories of Unicode?

answers.text: Letter, Mark, Number, Punctuation, Symbol, Separator and Other

qas.question: What type of use is the General Category not helpful for?

answers.text: not useful for every use, since legacy encodings have used multiple characteristics per single code point

qas.question: What is the General Category in Unicode?
How many General Category properties does each code point have?
What exists within the main Unicode categories?

plausible_answers.text: Letter, Mark, Number, Punctuation, Symbol, Separator

qas.question: What subcategories are found in the category Other?
Which category can always be used?

plausible_answers.text: legacy encodings have used multiple characteristics per single code point
